absyn

Class FieldAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • absyn.Absyn
      • absyn.Expression
        • absyn.Lvalue
          • absyn.FieldAccess

  • public class FieldAccess
extends Lvalue
    A node of abstract syntax representing the access to the field of an object. Its concrete syntax is the receiver.f notation.
    Author:
    Fausto Spoto

        Parameters:
        pos - the position in the source file where it starts the concrete syntax represented by this abstract syntax
        receiver - the abstract syntax of the receiver of the field access, that is, of the expression that is on the left of the dot in the receiver.f notation
        name - the name of the field which is accessed, that is, the symbol f on the right of the dot in the receiver.f notation

      • translate

        public Block translate(CodeSignature where,
                       Block continuation)
        Translates this expression into its intermediate Kitten code. The result is a piece of code which pushes onto the stack the value of a field of an object. Namely, the code that is generated is

        translation of receiver
        getfield field

        followed by the given continuation.
        Specified by:
        translate in class Expression
        Parameters:
        where - the method or constructor where this expression occurs
        continuation - the code executed after this expression
        Returns:
        the code that evaluates this expression and continues with continuation
